&lt;p&gt;Hone is looking for a Sr Data Engineer to join our team. In this role, you will report to the Sr. Director, Data, Analytics, and Machine Learning and you will help build the pipelines and infrastructure that power analytics, reporting, and machine learning. You will also build an longevity ontology knowledge graph. You’ll work cross-functionally with engineering, data, and business teams to design and implement reliable, well-tested data pipelines and scalable models. This role is ideal for someone with 5+ years of experience who’s ready to deepen their impact and technical scope in a fast-paced, collaborative environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Primary Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Key responsibilities for this role include (but are not limited to) the following:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build, maintain, and optimize reliable data pipelines using SQL, dbt, and Python.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build, maintain, and optimize an ontology graph database using CosmosDB and Gremlin.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Utilize agentic AI to automate pipeline development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Analytics Engineers, Data Scientists, Analysts and Software Engineers to move, transform, and structure data to meet business needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement data testing, observability, and documentation to ensure data reliability and transparency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in sprint planning and project estimation by breaking down work and communicating blockers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support scalable data model development in the lakehouse, balancing performance, flexibility, and usability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain and improve our data infrastructure, including orchestration and CI/CD pipelines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify opportunities to automate manual data workflows and reduce data-related tech debt.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor data quality and partner with engineering and product teams to fix upstream issues.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to dbt model development and refactoring, following best practices and company conventions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage cloud data environments (e.g., Azure) and optimizing resource usage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide thoughtful code reviews and mentor junior teammates on data engineering concepts and tooling.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In order to qualify for this role, candidates must meet the following criteria:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of industry experience in a data engineering, analytics engineering role, or ontology engineering role.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1+ years of industry experience building medical ontologies in a graph database (e.g. CosmosDB or Neo4j)&lt;/li&gt;
